Liverpool have opened an 11-point gap between themselves and champions Manchester City. The Reds, who finished with 10 men at Anfield, beat Brighton 2-1 on Saturday. Virgil van Dijk scored both goals, before Lewis Dunk pulled one back, after Alisson Becker was sent off for handball. In the early kick off, Manchester City were held to a 2-2 draw at Newcastle United. Chelsea lost 1-0 to West Ham at Stamford Bridge, with Aaron Cresswell scoring the only goal in the second half. Crystal Palace won 2-0 away at Burnley and Tottenham Hotspur saw off Bournemouth 3-2. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.